&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Epic&#39;s Education &amp;amp; Learning team provides accessible ways for current and aspiring creators to learn the real-time 3D tools and skills they need to be successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Director of Education &amp;amp; Training you will lead a team that is passionate about learning and driven to engage with educators and students--whether in an academic setting or through professional growth. You will set the strategy for growing adoption of Epic tools in educational markets and providing learning content that meets the needs of an evolving market, showcasing Epic’s latest technical capabilities. You will also engage regularly with educators and users through events and programs that tap into high-growth opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accelerate adoption in target markets via institutional partnerships and curriculum support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Oversee tool-specific bootcamps focused on career tracks and industry showcases&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Drive a Train-the-Trainer program to scale technical instruction globally through external partners&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Oversee regional initiatives to boost local markets, grow adoption, and increase Epic&#39;s visibility through events and speaking engagements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Foster engagement by collaborating with the Community team to facilitate programs, deliver content, and encourage community-led learning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Set strategy and vision for enabling infrastructure including tooling (Interactive Partner Directory, LMS) and certification pathways that promote and reward learning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Establish and track metrics that gauge effectiveness of programs and content&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
